{
  "text": "In order to provide evidence on the interaction of the two marine polysaccharides upon nanoparticle production, infrared spectroscopy was performed. From the analysis of Figure 1 , it is possible to monitor the presence of fucoidan and chitosan in the nanoparticles. The typical spectrum of fucoidan with S=O asymmetric stretching between 1160 and 1260 cm −1 and C-O-S stretching of the sulfate groups at 845 cm −1 can be observed in Figure 1 [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
